POLICE in Katavi region in collaboration with game rangers from Katavi National Park have arrested Mashaka Mavunje (42) in possession of two elephant's tusks weighing 3.1 kilogrames and a carcass of the jumbo weighing 90 kilogrammes. The Katavi Regional Police Commander (RPC) Mr Ali Makame Hamad confirmed the apprehension of Mavunje, a resident of Mtakuja Village in Mpanda District. He is described as a notorious poacher. According to police, the suspect was arrested at Kashoka area inside the Katavi National Park on April 14th, this year at around 2:00 pm. The suspect, apart from being caught red handed in possession of government trophy, he was also found in possession of a home-made gun (gobore)’, a machete and a sword. “His apprehension was made possible following a tip off from whistle blowers," noted the RPC. He further emphasized that the suspect will be arraigned to court after preliminary investigations are completed.